Math_Problem:
Find the least positive integer $n$ for which there exists a set $\{s_1, s_2, \ldots , s_n\}$ consisting of $n$ distinct positive integers such that
\[ \left( 1 - \frac{1}{s_1} \right) \left( 1 - \frac{1}{s_2} \right) \cdots \left( 1 - \frac{1}{s_n} \right) = \frac{51}{2010}. \] Let $d = s - 67$, where $s$ is the maximum element in such a minimal set. Determine the polynomials P of two variables so that:

a.) for any real numbers $t,x,y$ we have $P(tx,ty) = t^n P(x,y)$ where $n$ is a positive integer, the same for all $t,x,y$;

b.) for any real numbers $a,b,c$ we have $P(a + b,c) + P(b + c,a) + P(c + a,b) = d$;

c.) $P(1,d) =1.$

Let $f: \mathbb{N} \rightarrow \mathbb{N}$ be a function satisfying the following conditions:
(1) $f(1)=1$;
(2) $\forall n\in \mathbb{N}$, $3f(n) f(2n+1) =f(2n) ( 1+3f(n) )$;
(3) $\forall n\in \mathbb{N}$, $f(2n) < 6 f(n)$.
Find all solutions of equation $f(k) +f(l)=293$, where $k<l$.
($\mathbb{N}$ denotes the set of all natural numbers). Let $t = f(47) - 278$, where $f(47)$ is the value of the function at $47$ derived from the recursive relations. Let $a,b,c,d,e\geq  -1$ and $a+b+c+d+e=t.$ Find the maximum and minimum value of $S=(a+b)(b+c)(c+d)(d+e)(e+a).$

